# Forge — HA (#10 Wave A) load-balancer config (Caddy v2), used ONLY under docker-compose.ha.yml.
# =============================================================================================
# Fronts N `forge` replicas (Docker DNS `forge` round-robins to the replica IPs)
# behind ONE published endpoint. SSE endpoints (run logs, presence) must stay pinned to a single
# backend for the life of the stream, so the balancer is STICKY by cookie (`lb_policy cookie`):
# once a client is assigned a backend, a `lb` cookie keeps it there. Active health checks GET
# /health every 5s and drop an unhealthy replica from rotation — this is what makes the lease
# FAILOVER visible end-to-end (kill the leader container -> its /health stops answering -> Caddy
# routes to the survivor, whose /health flips leader:true within the lease TTL).
#
# HOST-ALLOWLIST NOTE: the console runs an anti-DNS-rebinding host guard (421 on an unknown Host).
# Caddy's reverse_proxy PRESERVES the client Host for proxied traffic (so client `Host: localhost`
# / `127.0.0.1` are accepted by the default allowlist), but Caddy's ACTIVE health probe sends
# `Host: forge:7100` (the upstream address). The HA compose therefore sets
# FORGE_CONSOLE_HOST=forge so the probe is accepted (200) instead of 421 — otherwise every
# backend would be marked unhealthy and the LB would 502.
:80 {
	reverse_proxy forge:7100 {
		lb_policy cookie
		health_uri /health
		health_interval 5s
	}
}
